    "encrypted": "false",
    "title": "Reflecting on Debugging Strategies",
    "long_instructions": "<div style=\"background-color: #026C7A; color: #FFFFFF; padding: 15px; border-radius: 10px; width: 90%; margin: 20px auto;\">\r\n    \r\n<p style=\"font-size: 44pt; font-weight: bold; margin: 0; text-align: center;margin-top: 15px;\">🎉🎉🎉</p><br>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 24pt; font-weight: bold; margin: 0; text-align: center; margin-top: 15px;\">Congratulations!</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 10px;text-align: center;\">\r\n        You've finished the third lesson in this professional learning module! <br><br><b> Advanced Algorithms with Python</b> is up next! \r\n    </p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<table width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"15\">\r\n    <tr>\r\n        <td style=\"background-color: #b2dee3; text-align: center;\"><b>Lesson One</b><br>Teaching Intro to <br>Programming</td>\r\n        <td style=\"background-color: #b2dee3; text-align: center;\"><b>Lesson Two</b><br>Compuational <br> Thinking</td>\r\n        <td style=\"background-color: #b2dee3; text-align: center;\"><b>Lesson Three</b><br>Python<br> Basics</td>\r\n        <td style=\"background-color: #f7f8fa; text-align: center;\"><b>Lesson Four</b><br>Advanced<br>Algorithms</td>\r\n        <td style=\"background-color: #f7f8fa; text-align: center;\"><b>Lesson Five</b><br>Preparing for the<br>Final Project</tr>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n## Anticipating Student Struggles\r\n\r\n#### Take a minute to reflect on how you introduce debugging strategies in your Python lessons. \r\n\r\n#### Consider the challenges your students might face, how you can encourage persistence, and ways to create a supportive learning environment where debugging is seen as a valuable skill rather than a frustration.\r\n \r\n>- #### What common errors or misconceptions might beginners face when learning Python, and how can I prepare to address them?\r\n>- #### How can I create a classroom environment where making mistakes is seen as a normal and valuable part of learning?\r\n>- #### What signs might indicate that a student is frustrated or stuck, and how can I intervene in a way that supports their learning without giving them the answer too quickly?\r\n>- #### How can I model a positive and systematic approach to debugging so that students see it as a natural part of coding? \r\n\r\n#### *These questions are just starting points for reflection and discussion — there is no need to answer all of them. Focus on the ones that resonate most with your teaching experience and goals.*\r\n\r\n\r\n<details style=\"background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;\">\r\n    <summary style=\"font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold;\">📝 Share in the forum!\r\n</summary>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px; padding-bottom:20px;\">\r\n    <p>\r\n\r\n####Participating in the <a href=\"https://forum.code.org/t/about-the-cs-ai-foundations-category/40251?u=plteam\" target=\"_blank\">Computer Science and AI Foundations PL Community</a> is optional and not necessary to earn a certificate for this module. However, we encourage you to engage with the broader Computer Science learner community. Please share your response to this reflection in the forum and take the time to read and respond to other educators' posts.\r\n*update link*\r\n### <a href=\"https://forum.code.org/t/reflecting-on-your-experience-with-codap/40257?u=plteam\" target=\"_blank\">Direct Link to this Forum Topic</a>\r\n\r\n\r\n</p></div>\r\n</details>\r\n",
